assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: HOMAG Group AG manufactures and sells machines and solutions for woodworking and timber construction industries worldwide. The company offers machines for storage system, cutting, sizing and edge banding, planning and moulding, drilling and fitting insertion, consulting services, assembly, packaging, automation, and house construction applications, as well as buffer and collating, sanding machines, and lacquering and laminating. It also provides CNC routers for sawing, routing, cutting, connecting, drilling, separating, milling, glue edges, edge finishing, measuring, and 3D machining applications. In addition, the company develops and sells software; and provides life cycle, field, remote, spare part, training, modernization, and financial services. HOMAG Group AG was founded in 1960 and is headquartered in Schopfloch, Germany. HOMAG Group AG operates as a subsidiary of Dürr Aktiengesellschaft.
